----------------------------------------------------------------
PRACTICAL 1(b): Create a Flowchart Based Project
----------------------------------------------------------------

AIM:
To create a flowchart-based project in UiPath that uses decision
(Flow Decision) nodes to implement a number-guessing game.

THEORY:
A Flowchart in UiPath allows non-linear execution using decision
nodes (Flow Decision). It is represented visually with a Start node,
activities, and diamond-shaped Flow Decision nodes for branching.
Flow Decisions evaluate a Boolean condition and branch to True/False.

STEPS:

Step 1: Create a New Project
  - Open UiPath Studio.
  - Click "New Project" > "Process".
  - Name it: a_flowchart_based_project
  - Click "Create".

Step 2: Change Workflow Type to Flowchart
  - In the Activities panel, search for "Flowchart".
  - Drag "Flowchart" onto the blank Main.xaml canvas.
  - OR: Right-click the canvas > select "Add Activity" > "Flowchart".
  - A green "Start" bubble will appear at the top.

Step 3: Set a Variable for the Secret Number
  - At the bottom of the Designer, click "Variables" tab.
  - Create a variable:
      Name: secretNumber    Type: Int32    Default: 7
  - Create another variable:
      Name: guessStr        Type: String
  - Create another variable:
      Name: guess           Type: Int32

Step 4: Add an Input Dialog Activity
  - In the Activities panel, search "Input Dialog".
  - Drag it into the Flowchart canvas below Start.
  - Connect Start to Input Dialog by hovering over Start, then
    dragging the arrow to the Input Dialog box.
  - In Properties:
      * Dialog Title:  "Number Guessing Game"
      * Input Label:   "Guess a number between 1 and 10:"
      * Input Type:    Text Box
      * Value Entered: guessStr

Step 5: Add an Assign Activity to Convert String to Int
  - Drag an "Assign" activity below the Input Dialog.
  - Connect Input Dialog to Assign.
  - In Properties:
      * To:    guess
      * Value: Int32.Parse(guessStr)

Step 6: Add a Flow Decision (First Decision)
  - Search "Flow Decision" and drag it onto the canvas.
  - Connect the Assign activity to this Flow Decision.
  - In Properties, set Condition: guess = secretNumber

Step 7: Add Message Box for Correct Guess (True Branch)
  - Drag a "Message Box" activity onto the canvas.
  - Connect the True arrow of Flow Decision to this Message Box.
  - In Properties:
      * Text: "Congrats, you guessed the right number !!"

Step 8: Add a Second Flow Decision (False Branch - Too High/Low)
  - Drag another "Flow Decision" onto the canvas.
  - Connect the False arrow of the first Flow Decision to it.
  - In Properties, set Condition: guess < secretNumber

Step 9: Message Box for Too Low (True Branch of 2nd Decision)
  - Drag a "Message Box" and connect to True of 2nd Flow Decision.
  - Text: "Your guess is too low. Try again!"

Step 10: Message Box for Too High (False Branch of 2nd Decision)
  - Drag a "Message Box" and connect to False of 2nd Flow Decision.
  - Text: "Your guess is too high. Try again!"

Step 11: Run the Project
  - Press F5 to run.
  - Enter a number when prompted.
  - If correct: "Congrats, you guessed the right number !!"
  - If wrong: appropriate message appears.

EXPECTED OUTPUT:
  If the user enters 7 (the secret number):
  "Congrats, you guessed the right number !!"

